(302002, 9682, 301558, 'colt 1911', 2444, '', 1348427053, '[QUOTE=Skeeter60;301558]This is not a problem. All Semi automatic shotguns have FREE FLOATING INERTIA  Firing Pins. When you let the bolt slam forward the firing pin moves forward due to inertia and lightly touches the primer, this causes a light mark and nothing more. It is safe and will never fire a cartridge. When the the hammer strikes it on firing, the  pin moves forward with a lot of acceleration and only then the primer is initiated to fire the cartridge. If you want to confirm;  take a fresh cartridge put it in the magazine tube and move the bolt slowly forward by hand instead of letting the bolt slam forward with the power of the recoil spring. \nYou will find there will be no mark now.[/QUOTE]\n\ndoes this happen in case of baikal mp 442 also?', 1, 0, '182.177.45.247', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 0, 0),
