(302685, 9849, 302659, 'shahid khan rarasham', 6253, '', 1348595422, '[QUOTE=12GAUGE;302659]Bro, kindly explain why you need molybdenum disulphide grease? then we can better guide you how to acquire it or some alternate product.\n\nif you are looking for molybdenum disulphide as a firearm lubricant then I would suggest that you can go to any local liquimoly dealer in your city and ask for moly grease LM402 (I could be wrong on the part number). \n\nthat grease is available in tube type packaging in NLGI-2 grade. you need either grade 0 or grade 1. Grade 2 is too think for a firearm and can potentially slow down the movement of the moving parts which may cause reliability/cycling/feeding issues. \n\nwhat you need is grade 0 (Grade Zero) which is the consistency of mayonnaise. since grade 0 is hardly ever available in the market, you can make your own. just mix any quality gun oil with the grease and thin the grease down to mayonnaise consistency.\n\nRegards.[/QUOTE]\n\ni need moly lube for tuning my diana panther 31 airgun so plz suggest me one for this,....', 1, 0, '111.68.102.24', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 0, 0),
