(303011, 1786, 302555, 'Ahmad82', 7755, '', 1348667413, '[LEFT][COLOR=#3C605B][FONT=Times New Roman][B]I have a Bird in spring [COLOR=#000000]by Emily Dickinson[/COLOR][/B][/FONT][/COLOR][/LEFT]\n 						[FONT=Arial] 						I have a Bird in spring\nWhich for myself doth sing --\nThe spring decoys.\nAnd as the summer nears --\nAnd as the Rose appears,\nRobin is gone.\n\nYet do I not repine\nKnowing that Bird of mine\nThough flown --\nLearneth beyond the sea\nMelody new for me\nAnd will return.\n\nFast is a safer hand\nHeld in a truer Land\nAre mine --\nAnd though they now depart,\nTell I my doubting heart\nThey''re thine.\n\nIn a serener Bright,\nIn a more golden light\nI see\nEach little doubt and fear,\nEach little discord here\nRemoved.\n\nThen will I not repine,\nKnowing that Bird of mine\nThough flown\nShall in a distant tree\nBright melody for me\nReturn.						[/FONT]', 1, 1, '217.165.48.245', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 0, 0),
